    <h1>Reconstruction fibers and diffusion displacement trajectories: tractography</h1>
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
  <p>
  Diffusion MRI is a unique modality to perform 'in-vivo dissection' of the brain. The reconstructed streamlines are estimates of plausible trajectories from the diffusion signal point of view.
  The underlying assuption is that diffusion signal is somehow dependent of  both the geometry and  the microstructure of the fibers.
  Several ways are available to reconstruct the geometry of these "virtual fibers":
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>local tractography: see <a href="bvprocess://tractography"><bvProcessName name="tractography"/></a> <a href="bvshowprocess://tractography"><img src="../../images/icons/icon_process.png" border="0"/></a> </li>
    <li>global tractography: incoming ! </li>
  </ul>
    <h2>How to use the tractography module?</h2>
    <h3>Local tractography</h3>
    <ul>
      <li> Get spherical harmonics representation of an ODF using local model pipelines:<a href="bvshowprocess://CSDReconstructionPipeline"><img src="../../images/icons/icon_process.png" border="0"/></a> </li>
      <li> Generate seeds using one of the seeding processes see <a href="bvcategory://diffuse/tractography/seeding"><bvProcessName name="seeding"/></a></li>
      <li> Go for either deterministic or probabilistic local tracking using <a href="bvshowprocess://tractography"><img src="../../images/icons/icon_process.png" border="0"/></a></li>
    </ul>
  </xhtml>
